import React from 'react'
import Navbar from "./Navbar"
import {Box, Grid, Card, CardActionArea, CardMedia, CardContent, Typography} from "@material-ui/core"
import {makeStyles} from "@material-ui/styles"
import {fypImage} from "../images/fyp.png"

const useStytles = makeStyles({
    particalesCanva : {
        position : "absolute",
        
    }
})

function Portfolio() {
    const classes = useStytles({

    })

    return (
        <>
            <Box component="div">
                <Navbar></Navbar>
                <Grid container justify="center" alignItem="center">
                    <Grid item xs={12} sm={8} md={6}>
                    <CardActionArea>
                    <CardMedia component = "img" alt=" Final year proejct of cityu" heigt='140'  image={fypImage}>
                    </CardMedia>
                    <CardContent>
                        <Typography gutteBottom variant="h5">
                            Fuzzy Logic Trading System
                        </Typography>
                        <Typography variant="body2" color="textSecondary" component="p">
                        Now day trading in finance product is very common in public. In the general financial market
                         whatever in the stock market, future market or forex market. Technical analysis is very popular
                          for investors. They will use these indicators such as MACD, RSI and KDJ so on for determining the 
                          direction of a trend, buy or sell.Unfortunately, these indicators are always malfunction
                           because of dichotomy - buy or sell only. Moreover, the markets change quickly, therefore, 
                           indicators are difficult to follow. In another aspect, Fuzzy logic is a form of many-valued 
                           logic in which the truth values of variables may be any real number between 0 and 1 inclusive. 
                           It is employed to handle the concept of partial truth, where the truth value may range between
                            completely true and completely false. For this theory, the indicator will be combined with fuzzy 
                            
                            logic, just can help to find out a trading balance for improving performance.
                        </Typography>
                    </CardContent>
                        <CardActions>
                            <Button size="small" color="primary">
                                Visit in GitHub
                            </Button>
                        </CardActions>
                     </CardActionArea>
                    </Grid>
                </Grid>
            </Box>
        </>
    )
}
 
export default Portfolio;
